texts.text: ...Found it. It has to be that.
>In a dimly lit warehouse, a demon draws a magic circle...
Uh, what's it doing...
...Nothing good, I imagine.
That magic circle has evil written all over it.
I have to think it's black magic and...
It can't be a coincidence that we're on top of a huge Dragon Stream.
It shouldn't have a big impact on the world,
but it might be enough to alter the way people think and feel.
Is that so...?
Enough to pit one another in a violent struggle?
It's possible. That's also probably not the whole story.
Such evil...!
Calamity... Malediction...
Take the soul of this untainted child and let disaster reign over this world...
*Snicker*
>From Rangda's hands, a glowing ball of light appears.
That... So this is the evil creature in possession of the missing piece.
Defiling the dead, and manipulating others with this evil ceremony...
By my name, there shall be punishment!
>Sraosha flies forward!
*Roar*
What... Who are you?
Why do you interrupt my ceremony?
No more talk. Relinquish that soul to me at once.
Oh, relinquish you say?

*Cackle*
I see, I see!
You're that girl.
But I killed you and took your soul.
How...?
Oh, I see. You're just a remnant!
...That's my soul, right? I'm here to take it back.
Take it back? After already losing to me?
*Sob*
I-I won't lose again! This time... I'm not alone!
That's right! We came to kick your ass!
I hope you're ready. We're no pushovers!

*Chuckle*
Then so it shall be!
I'll turn you all into sacrifices for my ceremony!
>Demons spew out of the magic circle...!
Here they come!
>The fight against Rangda rages on...
*Cackle*
*Wince*
Oh no you don't!
*Groan*
Are you alright? Leave first aid to me!
...! Thanks!

*Growl*
...!
Don't look away. You're fighting me, right?
It's now or never! Let's get the boss!
Y-Yeah!
>Ririn and the girl make their way towards Rangda!

*Puff*
Such impudence...!!
*Scream*
Shit, I'm...!
*Puff*
...Sraosha!
...! Stop interfering...!
Now's your chance! Go!
Yes! Devil Download!
*Scream*
>Rangda begins to disappear.
We... We did it! We won! We won!
>The ball of light falls away from Rangda,
>and slowly gravitates towards the girl.
Huh... What the?! I'm glowing...
Your soul has been made whole. Luckily, we weren't too late.
Too late?
...Truth be told, you were on the verge of disappearing.
Without the help of these Devil Downloaders,
you likely would have run out of time.
Oh, really...
However, now that your soul is once again whole, you are now properly dead.
Your time in this world is coming to an end.
...Right. It's okay. I don't think I have any regrets.
>The girl turns your way.
Thanks for helping me out.
For giving me a hand when I had a hard time asking for it,
thank you.
For not letting me be such a lonely Dx2,
and letting me be a Liberator like you guys, thank you!
I hope you'll always be this nice!
>The girl takes Sraosha's hand and starts to fade...
>They vanish completely and the girl's phone makes a cracking noise as it falls to the ground.
>It expends its last ounce of energy and turns off.
*Sob*
Ririn. Please don't cry.
I... I know. I know but...
It just hard when they could've been your little brother or sister.
It's frustrating... I just wanted her to live her life a little more.
Ririn. You're so kind.
I really do like that part of you!
...Yeah, and if only you were a beautiful, muscly girl, Jeng Yun.
But thanks. I'm okay now!
There's still a problem though...
Not being able to contact HQ or the other Branches is serious.
That girl's Branch may or may not have been the only one that was affected.
It's too hard to say for sure...
We were fine so it's alright.
We trusted in each other, worked together and made it this far.
And it won't change any time soon!
Of course
You never know
Yeah!
Even this time, we saved that kid because we worked together!
I guess in the end, you're all someone I can rely on.
Yes. We're ten times stronger when we work together.
My favorite heroes all protect this world by doing just that.
Together as one!
Well, we're not heroes or anything though.
[sys user_name], you're so harsh.
I'm amazed you can say something like that in this situation.
But there may be arguments from time to time.
We are strangers, technically.
If that happens, we just need to make sure they don't stay unresolved.
Oh... So you mean...
We should come to an understanding by duking it out by the river!
I always wanted to do that!
I'm not sure anyone will join you, Jeng Yun...
But after all that crying, I'm starved!
Me too. Let's get something to eat!
>The girl's phone still sits on the ground.
>You pick it up,
>stick it in your pocket and rejoin the others.
